text: Grace Chinonyelum Anigbata (born 16 September 1998) is a Nigerian track and field athlete who specialises in the triple jump. She competed at the 2019 African Games in the triple jump winning a gold medal. In 2016, Grace Anigbata became Nigeria's high jump champion at age 18, with a jump of 1.70 m. In 2018, she won the triple-jump event of the African championships in Asaba. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Living people Category:1998 births Category:Nigerian female long jumpers Category:Nigerian female sprinters Category:Nigerian female triple jumpers Category:Nigerian female high jumpers Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2019 African Games Category:African Games competitors for Nigeria Category:African Games gold medalists for Nigeria Category:African Games medalists in athletics (track and field) Category:African Championships in Athletics winners Category:African Games gold medalists in athletics (track and field)
